# Pre-push checks

Before running any `git push`, always run these two commands in order from
the workspace root. Both must pass clean before pushing.

```bash
cargo fmt -- --check
cargo clippy -- -D warnings
```

If `cargo fmt -- --check` fails, run `cargo fmt` to fix it, then re-check.

If `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` fails, fix all errors and warnings before
pushing. Do not suppress warnings with `#[allow(...)]` unless there is a
clear documented reason.

After both pass, run the tests to confirm nothing is broken:

```bash
cargo test
```

Then push.

## Linux CI build dependencies

The Ubuntu CI jobs require `cmake` and `libcurl4-openssl-dev` to build
`rdkafka` (pulled in by `spear-lib`). These are installed in the workflow —
no action needed locally on macOS.

## Why

The CI lint job runs `cargo fmt -- --check` and `cargo clippy -- -D warnings`
and will fail the build if either is not clean. Fixing this after a push
wastes a CI run and leaves the main branch red.
